- Scenario 2; Cross Company - Invoicing and Posting --> If warehouse and Project is not in the same CC, rental fees will go through CC1000 as the 'Principal'; --> CC1000 pays rental fee to warehouse based on rental price --> CC1000 issue invoices to Project, based on Rental price

From WH point of view Step 1: Inbound team A identifies part of the items to be GR from the return outbound delivery. Step 2: Inbound team A deletes the delivery item lines from return outbound delivery. (VL02N) Step 3: Inbound team A creates new return delivery taking only the items that are deleted in Step 2. (YPS_TOOL_MAINT Return) Step 4: Inbound team A runs query OBD_SERIAL to identify serial numbers from the deleted item lines. Step 5: Inbound team A updates serial numbers to the new return delivery (VL02N) Step 6: Inbound team A creates T.O. for receiving into WH SLOC (where requires) Step 7: Inbound team A Post Goods Receipt (VL02N)
